# Python linting (Ruff only)

This repo uses **Python only** for code. Use **Ruff** as the single linter and formatter. Do **not** add Black, Flake8, isort, or Pylint as separate tools.

## Commands (always via uv)

- Fix issues Ruff can auto-fix, then report the rest: `uv run ruff check --fix .`
- Apply formatting: `uv run ruff format .`
- Strict verification without writing files: `uv run ruff check .` and `uv run ruff format --check .`

## When editing Python

After changing any `.py` file, run **`ruff check`** and **`ruff format`** on the touched paths (or the whole repo) before considering the task done.

## Pre-commit (most reliable local gate)

One-time per clone: `uv run pre-commit install`. Then every `git commit` runs Ruff via `.pre-commit-config.yaml`.

To run the same checks manually: `uv run pre-commit run --all-files`.

## Configuration

- **Single source of truth:** `[tool.ruff]` / `[tool.ruff.lint]` / `[tool.ruff.format]` in **`pyproject.toml`**.
- Do not add parallel config in `ruff.toml` or `setup.cfg` unless there is a strong reason.
